#Day2
Question: iven a string text, you want to use the characters of text to form as many instances of the word "balloon" as possible.

You can use each character in text at most once. Return the maximum number of instances that can be formed.

Example 1:
Input: text = "nlaebolko"
Output: 1

Example 2:
Input: text = "loonbalxballpoon"
Output: 2

Example 3:
Input: text = "leetcode"
Output: 0

Constraints:

1 <= text.length <= 104
text consists of lower case English letters only.

Approach
Here we first find out the frequency of the alphabet from the given string into this word.
and return the minimum number of times this get returned.

class Solution
{
    public int maxNumberOfBalloons(String text) 
    {
        // we have to form instances of word "balloon" from the text
        //String alpha = "balloon";
        //we need to find the frequency of each alphabet of each of instances.
        int freq[] = new int[26];
        for( char ch : text.toCharArray())
            freq[ch-'a']++;
       // how many balloon can we form
       int b=freq['b'-'a'];
       int a= freq['a'-'a'];
       int l= freq['l'-'a']/2;
       int o= freq['o'-'a']/2;
       int n=freq['n'-'a'];

       return Math.min(Math.min(Math.min(b,a),Math.min(l,o)),n);
   
    }
}
